Package: HEARTSVG
Type: Package
Title: HEARTSVG: a high-efficiency and robust method for identifying
        spatial expression patterns in large-scale spatial
        transcriptomic data
Version: 1.1.0
Author: Xin Yuan
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yuanxin_yx@sjtu.edu.cn>
Description: Finding spatially variable genes(SVGs) in large-scale spatial transcriptomic data.
        Furthermore, we developed the software HEARTSVG to provide an SVG auto-clustering 
        module for predictions of spatial domain and visualizations, allowing users to 
        discover novel biological phenomena.
License: GPL
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: TTR, stringr, fpp2, seasonal, cluster, poolr, Seurat,
        SeuratObject, spatstat, spatstat.utils, spatstat.geom,
        spatstat.data, spatstat.random, spatstat.linnet,
        spatstat.sparse, reshape2, data.table, dplyr, stringr, ggplot2,
        MASS, EnvStats, BreakPoints, plotly, plot3D, plyr, gprofiler2
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
NeedsCompilation: no
Packaged: 2023-03-23 12:02:03 UTC; Yuanxin
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
